<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06025e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06025e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06025e"> 25(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mary is lateborn</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">But when Anna drew nigh to a woman, she would thrust her far away, saying, &ldquo;Touch me not, for thou art barren, lest thine infirmity pass over to us, and our husbands hate us, because we have become childless as thou.&rdquo; In the same manner also, the men were saying the like words against Joachim. <small> James DeQincy Donehoo, <a name="APOCD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#APOCD"><cite title="source">Les The Apocryphal Life of Christ</cite></a> (1903) 9</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: That is, Mary is born relatively late in her mother Anna&apos;s life. The belief was that conceptions very late in life, and births in the case of women that have been barren, are usually attended with something wonderful. </mm> </dd></dl>
